Here's an example of a Discord bot using Discord.js v14 with one slash command, "ban". This code assumes that you have already set up a bot on the Discord Developer Portal and have the bot token.

First, you need to install the required packages:
```
npm install discord.js
```
Then, create a file named `index.js` and add the following code:
```javascript
const Discord = require('discord.js');
const client = new Discord.Client();
const fs = require('fs');

client.on('ready', () => {
  console.log(`Logged in as ${client.user.tag}!`);
});

client.on('message', msg => {
  if (msg.content.startsWith('?ban')) {
    msg.reply('You have been banned.');
    client.guilds.cache.find(guild => guild.id === 'YOUR_GUILD_ID').members.cache.find(member => member.id === 'MEMBER_ID').ban();
  }
});

client.login('YOUR_BOT_TOKEN');
```
Replace `'YOUR_BOT_TOKEN'` with your bot's token and `'YOUR_GUILD_ID'` with the ID of the guild where you want the ban command to work.

